explanation:
OS_CHECK_POINTER: macro used at function entry — need its expansion to verify it does not invoke any <string.h> functions or perform unsafe pointer dereferences.
OS_ObjectIdGetById: direct callee — its implementation must be checked for any use of string functions, and to understand how it initializes the token and handles the objid parameter (bounds/validity semantics).
OS_ObjectIdTransactionInit: immediate callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById — include to trace any string function usage inside the transaction initialization path.
OS_ObjectIdToArrayIndex: used by OS_ObjectIdGetById — required to see any indexing or string operations that could go out-of-bounds.
OS_ObjectIdConvertToken: used by OS_ObjectIdGetById — needed to inspect how the token is formed/used and whether string functions are used on token internals.
OS_ObjectIdTransactionCancel: used by OS_ObjectIdGetById — include to verify no string operations are performed in the error/cleanup path.
OS_ObjectIdRelease: direct callee — its implementation must be inspected for string function usage or side effects affecting buffer bounds.
OS_ObjectIdTransactionFinish: used by OS_ObjectIdRelease — include to check for string operations in the release/finish path.
OS_SelectSingle_Impl: direct callee that performs the select logic — most likely place for any usage of C library string functions (memset/memcpy/strlen/etc.); must be inspected in full.
OS_ObjectIndexFromToken: callee of OS_SelectSingle_Impl — needed to see how token is converted to an index and whether string functions are used on object data.
OS_DoSelect: callee of OS_SelectSingle_Impl — the select implementation may manipulate fd sets or buffers and could call string.h functions (memset/memcpy); include to verify safe accesses.
OS_object_token_t: type of token parameter — its layout/fields are needed to determine whether any string operations in callees access token internals beyond bounds.
osal_id_t: type of objid parameter — its representation may affect how indexing/conversion functions behave; include to ensure correct interpretation.
uint32 / int32: integer typedefs used by the function — include to confirm sizes for buffer lengths/indices and any signed/unsigned interactions relevant to bounds checks.
OS_SUCCESS: return-code constant used in control flow — needed to understand success vs error paths to know which code paths to inspect for string usage.
OS_LOCK_MODE_REFCOUNT, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_STREAM: constants passed into OS_ObjectIdGetById — include because they may influence which object arrays or code paths are used inside OS_ObjectIdGetById/convert functions, and therefore which code to inspect for string handling.

Rationale: To determine whether this function (or its direct callees invoked here) violates the MISRA rule about string.h bounds, the analysis must inspect all macros, callees, and the related token/type definitions that could contain or cause calls to standard string functions. The listed symbols cover the function-local checks, the object-id acquisition/release paths, the select implementation and its immediate helpers, and the type/constant definitions that affect which code paths and data layouts are exercised.
